.TH "regulator_bulk_force_disable" 9 "regulator_bulk_force_disable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regulator_bulk_force_disable \- force disable multiple regulator consumers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" regulator_bulk_force_disable
.BI "(int num_consumers "  ","
.BI "struct regulator_bulk_data *consumers "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "num_consumers" 12
Number of consumers
.IP "consumers" 12
Consumer data; clients are stored here.
\fIreturn\fP         0 on success, an errno on failure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This convenience API allows consumers to forcibly disable multiple regulator
clients in a single API call.
.SH "NOTE"
This should be used for situations when device damage will
likely occur if the regulators are not disabled (e.g. over temp).
Although regulator_force_disable function call for some consumers can
return error numbers, the function is called for all consumers.
